As for <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Ender's Game</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> as anime, if anything, it'd be too <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  under</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->stated for anime - if it's to be true to Ender's perspective (and the perspective of the reader as presented by OSC), there'd be only 2 scenes of violence (the two fights), and a lot of shots of Ender behind some console or another.<br>
<br>
The book is told completely from Ender's perspective.  (No, I don't want to see it as a first-person ... [Humorous thought: dating-sim?] type anime.)  From his perspective, he spends a lot of time in the Battle Room, playing the RPG in the game room and behind a desk in class or in the final sim.  Not a lot of action. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/utaerx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TaerX</A> at: 6/23/02 9:10:55 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/utaerx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TaerX</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(6/22/02 11:16:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1684.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: a</span><hr size=1> I second the vote for Haldeman's <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> The Forever War</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> as anime.  There was a 3-volume graphic novel (european style, not anime) about 10 years ago - very well done.<br>
